H0.text: 4 weeks is the approximate time at which the development of the respiratory system in the fetus begins.

H1.text: 2 weeks is when the development of the respiratory system in the fetus begins.

H2.text: 4 months is the approximate time when the development of the respiratory system in the fetus begins.

H3.text: The development of the respiratory system in the fetus begins at about 4 days.

A4.text: The lung bud appears in the ventral wall of the foregut about four weeks into development.
